      "content": "The consensus among climate scientists is that renewables alone cannot meet the global energy demand required to hit net zero by 2050 without massive, immediate investment in nuclear energy. While solar and wind are essential, they are intermittent and require storage solutions that are currently too expensive and energy-intensive to scale up quickly enough. Without the reliable baseload power that nuclear provides, the transition to a carbon-neutral grid would be far slower, leaving billions of people without access to affordable electricity.",
